		<div id="comment_body_65275663"><p><div class="quote"><p>other units are just noise - why does it matter to you that its a 6 volt, 12 volt, or 24 volt thingamabob?

It matters if your device needs a 6 volt, 12 volt or 24 volt power supply and doesn't work with a different voltage. <br> <br>
It's like an ancient 3 1/2" floppy disk. It doesn't matter how big it is; what matters is that a 3 1/2" floppy disk is a floppy disk that fits into a 3 1/2" floppy disk drive. Or button batteries where the size is printed on the batteries; you don't care about the actual size, you just care that you have the right size that fits your device.</p></div></div>
	</div>

