			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~Baron_Yam">Baron_Yam</a>  <span class="uid"><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~Baron_Yam">( 643147 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_65275847"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65275847"><p>Consumers will not measure the power of their electronics by the maximum current draw on a battery.</p><p>A standard for measuring average runtime from full charge is what really matters, mAh only matters when comparing two devices where the only difference between them is battery capacity.</p></div>
	</div>

